items.sentence: Does Tom think that he doesn't have to do that?
I think that you should ask Tom not to do that.
I think that we shouldn't allow Tom to do that.
I think that it's unlikely Tom would ever move.
I think that it's unlikely Tom will marry Mary.
Tom ran past Mary, without even looking at her.
Tom ran away, shouting at the top of his lungs.
Tom said that Mary paid for the ticket herself.
Every morning Tom goes for a walk with his dog.
Tom died without telling his secret to anybody.
